{"title_page": "Hacienda Del Sol Guest Ranch Resort", "text_new": "'''Hacienda Del Sol Guest Ranch Resort''' is a [[hotel]] in or near [[Tucson, Arizona]].\n\nIt dates from 1929.  It is one of only two surviving [[dude ranches]] in Tucson, where once there were 20 or so.\n\nIt was started as a ranch school for girls in 1929.  It was converted into a guest ranch in 1948.  It claims John Wayne,  Clark Gable, Spencer Tracy and Katharine Hepburn were among its guests.<ref name=hha-history>{{cite web|url=https://www.historichotels.org/hotels-resorts/hacienda-del-sol-guest-ranch-resort/history.php |title=Hacienda Del Sol Guest Ranch Resort:  History |publisher=[[Historic Hotels of America]] |accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt is a member of the [[Historic Hotels of America]].<ref name=hha>{{cite web|url=https://www.historichotels.org/hotels-resorts/hacienda-del-sol-guest-ranch-resort/ |title=Hacienda Del Sol Guest Ranch Resort |publisher=[[Historic Hotels of America]] |accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[White Stallion Ranch]], Tucson, Arizona, the other surviving one, also an HHA member\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.haciendadelsol.com/ Hacienda Del Sol Guest Ranch Resort], official website\n\n[[Category:Hotels in Arizona]]\n[[Category:Tucson, Arizona]]\n[[Category:Dude ranches]]\n\n{{Arizona-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Hacienda Del Sol Guest Ranch Resort''' is a [[hotel]] in or near [[Tucson, Arizona]].\n\nIt dates from 1929.  It is one of only two surviving [[dude ranches]] in Tucson, where once there were 20 or so.\n\nIt was started as a ranch school for girls in 1929.  It was converted into a guest ranch in 1948.  It claims John Wayne,  Clark Gable, Spencer Tracy and Katharine Hepburn were among its guests.<ref name=hha-history>{{cite web|url=https://www.historichotels.org/hotels-resorts/hacienda-del-sol-guest-ranch-resort/history.php |title=Hacienda Del Sol Guest Ranch Resort:  History |publisher=[[Historic 